t><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AH Yes</span><hr size=1> I'm still friggen 52; although, I'm almost through my fourth yellow.  One more yellow plus, and I'm done.<br>
<br>
On killing drakes, they're easy.  TBoots outrun them easily, so if the first snare doesn't take, outrun them turn and root, then snare.  If you're being chased by a non-snared drake, you really want to root it first, then try snaring it again.  Use Immobilize as it casts fastest.  <br>
<br>
They have to be really close to you to hit with the AoE DD/Dispell.  Keep crap buffs up.  I've died twice to  having my TBoots dispelled.  I've problably killed over 200 drakes.<br>
<br>
I killed my first drake at 48/49.  I didn't think I'd have the balls to even try, but I decided to give it a whirl.  Before 51, you want to keep them rooted because Conflag takes so blasted long to cast.  Always snare to make it easy to re-root when they break.  I've had them sit, rooted through all my Conflags and I've had them break with each.<br>
<br>
After 51, simply snare and use Draught of Fire.  It casts fast enough to hit them before they can get within casting range.  You do one Draught, run to range, cast another.  Can't get in two before the drake gets in AoE range.<br>
<br>
The biggest problem is making sure you don't agro another wyvern, drake or named.<br>
<br>
I don't even try Azureake or Yvolcarn because killing them is a faction hit.  I'm still Dubious and don't want to make myself KoS there.  If I agro either, I zone into SS.<br>
<br>
On rare occasions, I'll have the drakes warp right on top of me.  This happens if I cast on a drake that *just* passed over me.  I don't know why. <br>
<br>
Both drakes and wyverns will warp to their spawn points when almost dead.  For this reason alone, I never kite on the beach.  Running back up to the top area to find that warped critter is a pain, gives them lots of time to heal, and allows someone else to KS me because this also resets agro and who did damage.<br>
<br>
Dying in CS is no big deal.  There is always a cleric around or inbound.  If I have trouble getting a rez, I'll auction that I'll give a quest gem for a rez.  That brings the freaking anonymous clerics out of the cracks for sure.  I hate that because I never go anon.  Never.   I wish clerics would give me the same courtesy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=113.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=117.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=133.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=133.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=133.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=133.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option va